         <entry xml:id="anqlimon-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#anqliton-dlgenr"
                next="#antrope-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אנקלימון</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾnqlymwn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">anqlimon</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="49,9 first occurrence - Ox1 V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקלימון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="49,9 first occurrence - Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקליטין</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="49,9 first occurrence - K" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">סנקליטון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="49,9 first occurrence - Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקריטיריון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="49,9 second occurrence - K V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנקליטין</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="anqlimon-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">law</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false"/>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>liable to charge</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Medieval Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἐγκλήμων (?)</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     אמר ר' יהודה בר' סימון בשר ודם תולין לו אנקריטיריון מדוכס לאיפרכוס מאיפרכוס לאיסטרטלטיס ואת בשביל שאין לך מי יתלה לך אנקליטון אנקליטין לא תעשה משפט
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">49,9</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 510: 4</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="anqliton.html">אנקליטון</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אנקריטיריון</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דוכס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איפרכוס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איפרכוס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איסטרטלטיס</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        R. Yehuda be-R. Simon said: (Abraham pleaded thus:) ‘Even in the case of a human judge, an anqlimon can be made from the commander to the prefect and from the prefect to the governor; but you, because no appeal can be made from your judgment, will you not do justly? (cf. Freedman / Simon I 429)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Medieval Greek</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aalphabetic+letter%3D*e%3Aentry+group%3D10%3Aentry%3De%29gklh%2Fmwn"
                          type="entry">ἐγκλήμων</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               May be an independent reading of V and Ox 1 for GenR. Attested also in 
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">DtnR 2,29</bibl> (acc. to Mus. and
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 167 [55a: 12]</bibl>).
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 159ab</bibl> and
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 76a</bibl>, suggest Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἐγκλήμα</term> / <term xml:lang="grc">ἐγκλήματα</term>. For further literature see Sperber. Cf.
               <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="anqliton.html">אנקליטון</ref>,
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אנקריטיריון</ref>
            </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sperber (1984)</title>
                  <citedRange>49</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
